
Task
Opposite value in an array
You are given an array arr and some number num. Determine if the array contains the opposite of num, and if so, return its index. If there is no such element, return undefined.
Write a function called oppositeInArray that takes arr and num as arguments and returns the index of the opposite of num.
Example:
• the function oppositeInArray ([1, -2, 3, 5], 2) must return 1 (since the element arr [1] = -2 is the value opposite to the given number 2).
• the function oppositeInArray ([100, 36, 1, 50], -50) must return 3 (since the element arr [3] = 50 is the value opposite to the given number -50).
• function oppositeInArray ([10, 3, 8, 11], 11) must return undefined (there is no element -11 in the array).

Solution
function oppositeInArray (arr, num) {
 for (let i = 0; i <= arr.length; i ++) {
  if (arr [i] === -num)
  return i;
  }
 return undefined;
}
